l admissibility of cryptographic evidence." "Network-level security (TLS, certificate chains)." "Social consensus or reputation-based confidence."], :stakeholder-question "How can I verify that a protocol outcome was correct without\n  relying on any single authority, and how can I prove correctness\n  to a third party?", :summary "A stakeholder examines the evidence trail left by a protocol\n  interaction — scenario trace, invariant results, evidence chain,\n  canonical hashes — and determines whether the outcome is trustworthy.\n  Confidence comes from cryptographically verifiable evidence, not from\n  trust in any single actor."} #:concept{:assumptions [], :failure-modes [:failure/unmodelled-sink :failure/unmodelled-source :failure/double-counted-liability :failure/false-conservation-failure :failure/rounding-dust-unaccounted :failure/wrong-claimant-allocation :failure/hidden-shortfall :failure/stale-claimable-after-cancel], :id :robustness/protocol-value-conservation, :maps-to {:benchmark-domain :domain/protocol-value-conservation, :claims [:claim/funds-conserved :claim/slashing-conservation :claim/no-leakage-beyond-shortfall :claim/partial-fill-fairness :claim/yield-preserved-during-shortfall :claim/appeal-bond-adequacy :claim/no-over-slashing :claim/solvency-status], :evidence [:evidence/world-before :evidence/world-after :evidence/state-diff :evidence/claimable-classification :evidence/allocation-result :evidence/invariant-result :evidence/trace], :framework-concepts [:concept/conservation], :scenarios ["settlement release/refund scenarios" "yield shortfall scenarios" "partial-fill withdrawal scenarios" "resolver slashing scenarios" "appeal and bond custody scenarios" "cancellation/finality scenarios"]}, :name "Protocol value conservation and allocation", :out-of-scope [], :stakeholder-language "When value moves through the protocol, every unit should be explainable:\n    paid out, refunded, held, slashed, assigned as a fee, recorded as a\n    shortfall, deferred as a recognised claim, waived by rule, or tracked as\n    bounded residual dust. The benchmark should make it clear where value\n    went and whether the distribution followed the intended rule.", :stakeholder-question "When value moves through the protocol, every unit should be explainable:\n    paid out, refunded, held, slashed, assigned as a fee, recorded as a\n    shortfall, deferred as a recognised claim, waived by rule, or tracked as\n    bounded residual dust. The benchmark should make it clear where value\n    went and whether the distribution followed the intended rule.", :summary "Whether protocol value is fully accounted for, correctly classified,\n    and distributed according to explicit protocol rules across settlement,\n    yield, bonds, slashing, fees, shortfalls, deferred claims, residuals,\n    and cancellation paths.", :title "Protocol value conservation and allocation", :why-it-matters "Most serious protocol failures are value-accounting failures: value can\n    disappear, appear without a source, be counted twice, be assigned to the\n    wrong bucket, or be hidden as an implicit shortfall. This benchmark\n    dimension gives reviewers a direct way to inspect whether Sew's\n    value-moving mechanisms remain auditable under ordinary, adversarial,\n    and shortfall conditions."} #:concept{:assumptions [], :failure-modes nil, :id :allocation/partial-fill, :maps-to {:claims [:evidence-root-present :replay-result-present], :evidence [:evidence/settlement-path :evidence/value-transfer], :invariants [:yield/shortfall-splits :yield/value-conservation :allocation-complete], :scenarios ["S-DR-043-payout-shortfall-deferred"]}, :name "Partial fill allocation", :out-of-scope [], :stakeholder-language "If there is not enough value to pay everyone in full, the protocol should\n    distribute what is available in a predictable way.", :stakeholder-question "If there is not enough value to pay everyone in full, the protocol should\n    distribute what is available in a predictable way.", :summary "When available value is insufficient, the protocol pays the recoverable\n    portion of valid claims instead of pretending all claims can be satisfied.", :title "Partial fill allocation", :why-it-matters "This is the visible part of the benchmark's shortfall behavior: partial\n    recovery should remain fair and reproducible."} #:concept{:assumptions [], :failure-modes nil, :id :allocation/shortfall, :maps-to {:claims [:evidence-root-present :replay-result-present], :evidence [:evidence/shortfall :evidence/metrics], :invariants [:yield/shortfall-splits :yield/value-conservation :conservation], :scenarios ["S103_negative-yield-shortfall-cascade"]}, :name "Shortfall detection", :out-of-scope [], :stakeholder-language "The system should know when it cannot satisfy all valid claims and make\n    that deficit visible instead of silently dropping it.", :stakeholder-question "The system should know when it cannot satisfy all valid claims and make\n    that deficit visible instead of silently dropping it.", :summary "The protocol detects when the requested value exceeds what can be paid and\n    records that shortfall explicitly.", :title "Shortfall detection", :why-it-matters "If shortfall is not detected, later recovery logic cannot make a fair or\n    auditable allocation."} #:concept{:assumptions [], :failure-modes nil, :id :allocation/stake-liquidity-blocking, :maps-to {:claims [:evidence-root-present :replay-result-present], :evidence [:evidence/settlement-path :evidence/invariant-results], :invariants [:yield/shortfall-splits :yield/position-consistency :yield/exposure], :scenarios ["S104_resolver-stake-shortfall"]}, :name "Stake liquidity blocking", :out-of-scope [], :stakeholder-language "A resolver whose stake is caught in a shortfall should not be able to act\n    as if their full stake is available when it is not.", :stakeholder-question "A resolver whose stake is caught in a shortfall should not be able to act\n    as if their full stake is available when it is not.", :summary "When a resolver's protocol stake is affected by a yield module shortfall,\n    the protocol blocks actions that require liquid stake instead of allowing\n    them to proceed with insufficient coverage.", :title "Stake liquidity blocking", :why-it-matters "If shortfall-affected stake is treated as fully liquid, resolvers can take\n    actions that exceed their actual backing, undermining the safety of the\n    resolution system."}]}, :evidence/hash "96a63c1f33389ffb800a9688a1b700c90a36a0aa7dfc8be634ef076655a33d49", :run/manifest {:adapter "class resolver_sim.benchmark.runner.SewAdapter", :declared-run-count 1, :execution-count 3, :metrics {:declared-run-count 1, :execution-count 3, :passed 0, :passed-execution-count 0, :total 3, :unique-scenario-count 3}, :scenario-count 3, :scenario-hashes [{:file "resource:scenarios/edn/S-DR-043-payout-shortfall-deferred.edn", :outcome :fail, :benchmark/run-count 1, :benchmark/run-index 1, :scenario/evidence-root "6d658f955609476c898dd6f51a37c72f72e9cb32e3d9b58a62126f3445b01ca1", :scenario/id nil} {:file "resource:scenarios/edn/S103_negative-yield-shortfall-cascade.edn", :outcome :fail, :benchmark/run-count 1, :benchmark/run-index 1, :scenario/evidence-root "dd4367d3dacbbf90e041a295c3b3cd5f9af39323064c6a397e938c31ee7464ef", :scenario/id nil} {:file "resource:scenarios/edn/S104_resolver-stake-shortfall.edn", :outcome :fail, :benchmark/run-count 1, :benchmark/run-index 1, :scenario/evidence-root "574ae1ae581ceab921ca3deb4a768293fd67e7f36fc257c4d8742860ca9d9179", :scenario/id nil}], :unique-scenario-count 3, :benchmark/id :benchmark/prf-shortfall-allocation-v0, :benchmark/manifest-source "benchmarks/packs/prf-core/shortfall-allocation-v0.edn", :manifest/at "2026-07-09T13:13:47.703124510Z", :manifest/version "run-manifest.v1"}}